_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9184079590835404, \"rank\": 0.08451895324072049, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"Glorious golds\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"some shine\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"an otherwise disappointingParis2024\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"the Netherlands\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final haul of 14 golds was the lowest sinceAthensin 2004, and disappointment was especially palpable across traditionally big ticket sports such as cycling, sailing and boxing, which failed to deliver on their lofty pre-Games expectations.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final haul\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"14 golds\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"disappointment\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"traditionally big ticket sports\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 729}, {\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"sailing\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"boxing\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"their lofty pre-Games expectations\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless, inspiration came in plentiful supply, and no more high-profile than Hodgkinson, who belatedly emerged from a succession of major silver medals to see off her 800-metre rivals and burst to Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"score\": 0.999658358137964, \"rank\": 0.00034175862118314014, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 856}, {\"ngram\": \"plentiful supply\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"no more high-profile\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"a succession\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"major silver medals\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"her 800-metre rivals\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a sailing event blighted by a persistent lack of wind, Ellie Aldridge stole the show by becoming the first female champion in the high-octane sport of kite-surfing, the Olympic regatta's answer to the increasing urbanisation of the Games programme.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"score\": 0.9968576993947563, \"rank\": 0.003152129444616711, \"text\": \"Ellie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\"}, {\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9999695220991998, \"rank\": 2.9875049811684828e-05, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sailing event\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"a persistent lack\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"wind\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"the first female champion\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1173}, {\"ngram\": \"the high-octane sport\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"kite-surfing\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic regatta's answer\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"the increasing urbanisation\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games programme\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1298}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other sports seized their moments in the spotlight: Amber Rutter's dramatic skeet-shooting silver, just three months after giving birth, propelled her onto the front pages, while Page bounced to trampoline gold at the third time of asking.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other sports\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"their moments\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"Amber Rutter's dramatic skeet-shooting silver\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"the front pages\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"Page\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"the third time\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But a five-medal haul by Britain's equestrian team was overshadowed by controversy over dressage starCharlotte Dujardin, who was forced out on the eve of the Games after video footage emerged of her mis-treating a horse.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7199519689439193, \"rank\": 0.38897629761768154, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1577, \"end\": 1587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999034339564818, \"rank\": 9.657525488439445e-05, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a five-medal haul\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"dressage starCharlotte\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"Dujardin\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"video footage\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, the news narrative was hijacked by a gender row involving boxers Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting, both of whom would go on to win gold medals, and the questionable abilities of an Australian breakdancer called Raygun.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9996153048322767, \"rank\": 0.00018432785731644386, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1982, \"end\": 1988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.107938969667442e-27, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the news narrative\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1793}, {\"ngram\": \"a gender row\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"boxers\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris itself was lauded for bringing the Games back to the people by resisting the recent trend of Olympic Parks and placing the majority of their events in established venues within easy reach of the city's metro system.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1991, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0056059158578044e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2056}, {\"ngram\": \"the recent trend\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Parks\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"the majority\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"their events\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"established venues\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"easy reach\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's metro system\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It fostered a close relationship between the city and the ongoing Games programme which was badly needed after the awkward atmosphere of Covid-hit Tokyo in 2020, and the disappointingly soulless Games in Rio in 2016.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2361, \"end\": 2366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9992029774628137, \"rank\": 0.0007976542223857561, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.685879357178499e-15, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a close relationship\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2246}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2263}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing Games programme\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"the awkward atmosphere\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"the disappointingly soulless Games\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were plenty of reasons for the French public to celebrate, not least rugby union hero Antoine Dupont leading the hosts to gold in the men's rugby sevens event, and judo icon Teddy Riner snaring his third career gold on the mat at the Champ de Mars.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5685971631674726, \"rank\": 0.6140487501575215, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Antoine Dupont\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\"}, {\"begin\": 2612, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2449}, {\"ngram\": \"reasons\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"the hosts\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's rugby\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"sevens event\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"his third career gold\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"the mat\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2664}, {\"ngram\": \"the Champ de Mars\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For all its various mis-fires - not least a pair of spectacularly mis-judged ceremonies - there were some truly memorable moments, be it beach volleyball players serving in the shadows of the Eiffel Tower, or fencers and taekwondo stars descending the stairs of the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all its various mis-fires\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2717}, {\"ngram\": \"not least a pair\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2736}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacularly mis-judged ceremonies\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"some truly memorable moments\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"it beach volleyball players\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadows\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2872}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"fencers\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2904}, {\"ngram\": \"taekwondo stars\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"the stairs\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2946}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Palais\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lording it over the programme was the ubiquitousSnoop Dogg, clad in full riding kit for the dressage competition in Versailles, or declaring open the first and probably last Olympic breakdancing event, which for all of Raygun's worst efforts, went down well.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3085, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.712586743452054e-11, \"text\": \"Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 3188, \"end\": 3194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.107938969667442e-27, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the programme\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"the ubiquitousSnoop Dogg\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3027}, {\"ngram\": \"full riding kit\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"the dressage competition\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3081}, {\"ngram\": \"the first and probably last Olympic breakdancing event\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snoop played his part, via video link, in the closing ceremony too, presenting a timely reminder that the 2028 Olympics will be heading to his native Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 3229, \"to\": 3391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3379, \"end\": 3390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999997717168, \"rank\": 2.242104086373694e-10, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Snoop\", \"from\": 3229, \"to\": 3234}, {\"ngram\": \"his part\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"video link\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"a timely reminder\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3325}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympics\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite Great Britain's relative struggles, the Paris Games will take some beating.\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3400, \"end\": 3413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9947268565975166, \"rank\": 0.005301082594892602, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3451}, {\"ngram\": \"some beating\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3613, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3528}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 3532, \"to\": 3540}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3597}]}]}"